cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of detecting adversarial examples in deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a method based on non-linear dimensionality reduction, which is a technique commonly used in unsupervised learning and data visualization, suggesting that it could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
